<TITLE> Joy joins up </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Liakat Ali Badal bdnews24.com correspondent Rangpur, Feb 25 (bdnews24.com)Sajeeb Wazed Joy, son of prime minister Sheikh Hasina, has enrolled as a primary member of the Awami League from Rangpur, his ancestral home. The ruling party's joint general secretary, Md Mahbubul Alam Hanif, formally handed the membership document to the US-based grandson of the Bangladesh's founding president. At least four MPs watched as Hanif personally filled in the form and filed it with the party's district unit leaders amid applause from those present. "Joy is son of Rangpur," said Rezaul karim Razu, the district joint convenor. "As he formally joins the party, we want him to work for the welfare of the downtrodden in this region." Later, an extended meeting of the party's local unit formally approved his membership. b
